captions.text:
You remember that time I tried to teach you
how to be cool?
Mmm, hmm!
Well, it didn't work!
(Disappointed) Hmm...

Y'know those times when you're really excited
about something and you're like...

So, then I was all like IN YOUR FACE!!
And they were all like WOOOOOOAH!!
And I was all like I'M SO RANDOM!!
*slap*
Ouch!
Yeah... That's gotta stop.
So, while you're flailing about and yelling.
You're probably assuming that everyone around you is thinking...

"This person is awesome! Their expressive
hand gestures and body language clearly represent

their immense passion and interest in this
particular subject they are talking about."
What they're actually thinking is...

"AHHH! WHAT'S WRONG WITH THIS MANIAC?!! ARE
THEY ABOUT TO KILL ME?! IS THIS THE END OF

MY LIFE?! ARE THEY ABOUT TO MAKE ME DIE?!
AM I GOING TO BE DEAD SOON?!
I'M GOING TO DIE LIKE THIS!"

This is because you're moving way too much
way too fast.
Just because it's called your "personal space"
doesn't mean you should do whatever you want in it.
*Random clown type vocal noises*

See, if you're going crazy in your own little
area then to the person you're talking to
there is not much difference between...
"I LOVE VIDEO GAMES!!"
And...
"I LOVE STABBING PEOPLE!!"
So, by now you're probably asking...

(Girly voice) "But Tom! How can I not terrify
everyone around me?!"

Well, I'm glad you asked incredibly whiney
and effeminate representation of the person
watching this video.
Here is what you've got to do.
Take a lot of drugs.
*Smoking a fatty*

Just kidding, but you've got to tone it down...
A lot!
You see nobody wants to talk to the person
they think is going to scream and then punch them in the face.
Crazy, huh?

Do you ever wonder why people with hands in
their pockets are so cool?
It's because they're not shouting.
They actually can't.
What?

No, seriously. Try shouting with your arms
down.
You really won't want to do it after a while...
*Angry scream*
No! Arms down.
*Less angry scream*
Yeah, that's what I thought.

So, the next time you're in a large group
of people try keeping your arms to your side

and watch how people don't run away from you
screaming like little children.
Now go outside and make some friends!
Haha! Just kidding, you can't make friends.
